title: Grateful Dead Live at Community War Memorial Auditorium on 1980-09-02
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 2448 Tagged
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, Sugaree-> El Paso, Friend Of The Devil, It's All Over Now, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Althea, CC Rider, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Iko Iko-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Alabama Getaway

reviews.review_text: Great Dew!! The third of only four Morning Dew's for 1980. They barely played it back than. In the fall of 1981 they started playing it more regularly, until by 1987 it was all over the place.

Nice 24bit Upgrade-Thanks I LOVE Garcias' tones during these Fall '80 shows...Fat Fat Fat! This is version bring much more clarity and seperation but retains the awesome dynamics of the source. Definetly worth the MB's. Download and pass it on to future generations!!!
like this show. how pumped is the crowd to hear China/Rider 1 set?
